# JAQL C++ Standards

Full reference: [docs/coding-standards.md](docs/coding-standards.md)

## Language

- C++23 only. `CXX_EXTENSIONS OFF` — no GNU/MSVC extensions.
- Target: GCC 13+, Clang 17+, MSVC 2022.

## Naming

| Entity | Convention | Example |
|--------|------------|---------|
| Types, concepts | `PascalCase` | `YieldCurve` |
| Functions, variables | `snake_case` | `discount_factor()` |
| Private members | `snake_case_` | `settlement_date_` |
| Namespaces | `snake_case` | `jaql::rates` |
| Macros | `JAQL_SCREAMING_SNAKE` | `JAQL_ASSERT` |

## Error Handling

- Return `jaql::core::Result<T>` (`tl::expected<T, jaql::core::Error>`), always `[[nodiscard]]`.
- Propagate with `.map()` / `.and_then()` — never swallow errors.
- No throws for domain failures; exceptions for programmer errors only.

```cpp
[[nodiscard]] auto discount_factor(YearFraction t, Rate r) noexcept -> Result<double>;
```

## Strong Types & Concepts

- Use `StrongType<Tag, T>` for domain quantities (`Rate`, `Notional`, …).
- Use C++23 `requires` concepts — never SFINAE (`std::enable_if_t`).

## Headers

- `.hpp` / `.cpp`, `#pragma once` only.
- Include order: corresponding header → JAQL → third-party → standard library (alphabetical within each group).
